article.headline: Fla Atlantic 77, Stetson 62
article.story: BOCA RATON, Fla. (AP) -- DeAndre Rice and Carlos Monroe each scored 21 points as Florida Atlantic defeated Stetson 77-62 Monday. Florida Atlantic (6-7) improved to 5-1 in conference play and remained atop the Atlantic Sun Conference standings. Stetson (2-11, 2-3) had their two-game winning streak snapped. Rice hit four three-pointers in the first half while Monroe went 6-for-8 from the field to take Florida Atlantic to a 39-26 halftime lead. Florida Atlantic extended the lead to 21 in the second half before Stetson mounted a rally. Anthony Register's lay-up cut the deficit to 14, and Gabe McMillen's three-pointer pulled Stetson within 12. E.J. Gordon led Stetson with 15 points, while Will Holloman scored 11. Besides scoring 21 points for Florida Atlantic, Monroe had nine rebounds, while Rice went 5-for-6 from three-point range. Rodney Webb recorded a double-double with 12 points and 11 rebounds. Florida Atlantic shot 53 percent for the game and outrebounded Stetson 35-22.
